panels.description:
The number of completed stages in the job.

Can be used to monitor:  
    Job progress.  
    Per-stage timeline of job execution,when correlated with other metrics.
panels.title: Driver Completed Stages

panels.description:
The number of completed tasks in the job.

Can be used to monitor:  
    Job progress.  
    Parallelism within a stage.
panels.title: Driver Completed Tasks

panels.description:
The number of failed tasks.
  
Can be used to monitor:  
    Data abnormalities that cause job tasks to fail.  
    Cluster abnormalities that cause job tasks to fail.  
    Script abnormalities that cause job tasks to fail.
panels.title: Driver Failed Tasks

panels.description:
The number of tasks killed.  

Can be used to monitor:  
    Abnormalities in Data Skew that result in exceptions (OOMs) that kill tasks.  
    Script abnormalities that result in exceptions (OOMs) that kill tasks.
panels.title: Driver Killed Tasks

panels.description: The fraction of CPU system load used (scale: 0-1) for ALL executors.
panels.title: Executor System Load

panels.description: The fraction of CPU system load used (scale: 0-1) for the driver.
panels.title: Driver System Load

panels.description: The fraction of memory used by the JVM heap for this executor identified by executorId, or ALL executors.
panels.title: Executor JVM Usage

panels.description: The fraction of memory used by the JVM heap for this driver.
panels.title: Driver JVM Usage

panels.description: The number of bytes read from Amazon S3 by ALL executors since the previous report (aggregated by the AWS Glue Metrics Dashboard as the number of bytes read during the previous minute).
panels.title: Executor S3 Read Bytes

panels.description: The number of bytes read from Amazon S3 by the driver since the previous report (aggregated by the AWS Glue Metrics Dashboard as the number of bytes read during the previous minute).
panels.title: Driver S3 Read Bytes

panels.description: The number of bytes written from Amazon S3 by ALL executors since the previous report (aggregated by the AWS Glue Metrics Dashboard as the number of bytes written during the previous minute).
panels.title: Executor S3 Write Bytes

panels.description: The number of bytes written from Amazon S3 by the driver since the previous report (aggregated by the AWS Glue Metrics Dashboard as the number of bytes written during the previous minute).
panels.title: Driver S3 Write Bytes

panels.description: The number of megabytes of disk space used across all executors.
panels.title: Driver Disk Used
